  "title": "Cost Engineer / Pricing Analyst #81262",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Manufacturing</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Cost Engineer / Pricing Analyst</strong></li><li>Working Location: Tai Seng</li><li>Working Hours: 5 days (Mon – Fri, 8.00am – 6.00pm)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic salary up to $3,800 + AWS + Performance Bonus</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent Role</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Review customer inquiries, specifications, or requests for quotes (RFQs) to understand the project or product needs.</li><li>Calculate costs by reviewing labour, materials, time needed, and overhead costs.</li><li>Prepare clear and accurate price quotes, proposals, or bids on time.</li><li>Work closely with Sales, Production, Engineering, and Procurement teams to ensure quotes are accurate and workable.</li><li>Keep updated on pricing trends, market conditions, and material costs.</li><li>Communicate with customers to confirm requirements or discuss terms when needed.</li><li>Use quoting tools, spreadsheets, or ERP systems to create, update, and track quotes.</li><li>Ensure quotes follow company guidelines, target profit margins, and relevant industry standards.</li><li>Follow up on submitted quotes to support the Sales team in progressing opportunities.</li><li>Keep proper records of quotes, changes made, and customer communications.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>Relevant experience in quoting, estimating, or pricing analysis (industry-related experience is an advantage).</li><li>Strong number and analytical skills for cost calculation and pricing work.</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Excel and familiar with quoting software or ERP systems (e.g., SAP, Oracle).</li><li>Knowledge of industry materials, processes, or market trends is an advantage.</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#81262 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Angel Lim | EA Reg No.: R1769781</p>",
